         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>72</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>62</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1967a"/><citedRange>74</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>382 n.1</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... but Śuddhodana was a member of the reigning order (i.e., kṣatriya) like Karṇa</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... die zwei Frauen sind ... [herbei]zuführen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... the two women are ... to be brought [here].</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>382, fn. 1</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>382 and n.1</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>736</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">therefore the ministers proposed a request OR thereupon the ministers were called for (making) a request</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Daher stellten die (Minister) einen Wunsch frei.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Therefore the (ministers) granted a wish.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>382</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>312, 315</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>125</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:adams2012a"/><citedRange>26</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... she [scil. the sun] illuminates Jambudvīpa with a thousand rays ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Sobald (die Sonne im) Schosse des Sumeru aufgeht, erleuchtet sie mit tausend Strahlen Jambudvīpa ...</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">As soon as (the sun) rises (in) the depth of Sumeru, with a thousand rays it illuminates Jambudvīpa ...</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>137, 274</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
